Q1. What is the primary purpose of an Amazon ECS task definition when deploying an application? 
    1. To define the network configuration 
    2. To manage IAM roles 
    3. To set up auto-scaling policies 
 (v)4. To specify the container images to use

Q2. Which of the following is true about Amazon ECS services? 
 (v)1. They automatically restart failed tasks 
    2. They can only use the Fargate launch type 
    3. They require manual scaling 
    4. They can only run one task at a time

Q3. Which ECS feature allows you to run and maintain a specified number of instances of a task definition simultaneously in an ECS cluster? 
    1. Task 
 (v)2. Service 
    3. Deployment 
    4. Container Instance

Q4. What does the 'portMappings' section in an Amazon ECS Task Definition specify? 
 (v)1. The mapping between container ports and host ports 
    2. The ports used for container-to-container communication 
    3. The ports reserved for ECS service discovery 
    4. The ports open on the EC2 instance

Q5. After updating the task definition, what needs to be done to deploy the new version of the application in Amazon ECS? 
    1. Manually stop and start all tasks 
 (v)2. Update the ECS service to use the new task definition 
    3. Create a new cluster 
    4. Reboot all container instances
